            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-4">Nador West Med Port Project Overview</h2>

            <p class="mb-4">The Nador West Med port will consist of the following developments, which make up the project:</p>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-2">Protection Structures (5.4 km, reaching depths of approximately -35 m ZH):</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mb-4 space-y-1">
                <li>Main rubble mound breakwater: 4,200 linear meters</li>
                <li>Secondary rubble mound breakwater: 1,200 linear meters</li>
            </ul>

            <p class="mb-4">The breakwaters and the two head structures protect a water area of approximately 250 hectares, including a turning ellipse and a turning circle at -22 m ZH.</p>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-2">Berthing Structures:</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mb-4 space-y-1">
                <li>Two continuous East and West container terminals built on steel piles, totaling 2,960 linear meters at -20 m ZH</li>
                <li>The container terminals are located on both sides of a dock basin 500 meters wide</li>
                <li>East container yard behind the East quay, with an area of 76 hectares</li>
                <li>West container yard behind the West quay, with an area of 62 hectares</li>
                <li>Three oil berths located along the main breakwater at -20 m ZH, with mooring lengths of 118 meters</li>
                <li>One specialized bulk berth on piles at -20 m ZH</li>
                <li>One service quay 360 meters long, at depths of -7 m ZH</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-2">Nautical Access:</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">Access to the port is via an access channel 1,400 meters long, with depths of -22 m ZH, oriented SSW-NNE.</p>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-2">Quay Equipment:</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
                <li>Mooring bollards and quick-release hooks</li>
                <li>Ladders, fenders, and tie-downs for gantry cranes</li>
                <li>Gantry cranes</li>
                <li>Cranes and loading arms</li>
            </ul>
